{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Derive and enforce plan-material-pin health\n\n## Goal\nUse signed pins as the single related-material validity check across every attestation lifecycle consumer, while preserving safe rollout for existing projects.\n\n## Implementation\n- Add verify.enforce_plan_material_pins with default false and strict enabled-mode validation.\n- Own the nested DerivedPlanReviewHealth contract returned as health beside compute_plan_review_validity existing top-level {valid, reason, verdict}. It has pin_status exactly current, stale-pin-drift, stale-pin-missing, malformed-pin, or legacy-unpinned; enforced boolean; and targets: list[TargetPinDetail]. Child 5967 extends the same contract with phase_status and phase compatibility after it introduces the phase manifest format. TargetPinDetail is exactly {canonical_id: string, role: child|prerequisite, pinned_fingerprint: string, current_fingerprint: string|null, pin_status: current|stale-pin-drift|stale-pin-missing|malformed-pin}; legacy-unpinned has an empty targets list. Compare signed pins against current narrow material to populate it; all renderers consume this contract rather than duplicating strings.\n- When enabled, drift, malformed pins, or a deleted/missing pinned target invalidate the attestation. Archived targets remain readable. When disabled, report the same observations as advisory while valid remains true.\n- Treat a wholly unpinned legacy attestation as valid in either mode. Do not rewrite pins when configuration changes.\n- Own one compute_plan_review_validity profile boundary used by claim, reuse, drift refresh, re-sign, audit/health, and close. The claim profile checks code freshness. The close profile sets check_code_freshness=false while retaining signature, registry, own-material, and configured pin checks; child 5967 later adds phase compatibility to both profiles; the close story must call this profile rather than reimplement validity.\n- Keep optional unreadable configuration fail-open with a warning, matching existing gate posture; once enforcement is successfully enabled, validation fails closed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift invalidates the claim consumer.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift invalidates the close-profile consumer when that gate is active.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents idempotent attestation reuse.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents progressive drift refresh.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents re-sign.\n- [ ] Audit reports enabled pin drift as invalid.\n- [ ] Derived health reports enabled pin drift as invalid.\n- [ ] Disabled enforcement reports the same drift as advisory without changing valid.\n- [ ] Legacy unpinned attestations remain valid across configuration toggles.\n- [ ] verify.enforce_plan_material_pins=true leaves new pin emission enabled.\n- [ ] verify.enforce_plan_material_pins=false leaves new pin emission enabled.\n- [ ] Missing/deleted, archived, malformed, duplicate, and re-enable scenarios are deterministic.\n- [ ] No warning event is persisted for derived health.\n- [ ] Malformed manifest metadata returns malformed/invalid at every consumer without raising.\n\n## Verification\n- Run focused attestation invalidation, reuse, drift-refresh, re-sign, and config tests.\n- Run make check and the non-integration test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784536192433077001,"uuid":"f15eca25-96ae-4172-8254-82912de3b827"}